      • runMerge

        public java.lang.Object[] runMerge(int sortType,
                          boolean isDesOrd,
                          int tabLength,
                          int resultFormat,
                          java.lang.String before,
                          java.lang.String after)
                            throws quitada.MononovException
        Merge two java histogram files extracted with the following jmap command and sort result based on type of sorting in descending or ascending order.
        jmap -histo:live [target java pid]
        Parameters:
        sortType - Type of sorting: 0 - by instance /1 - by byte /2 - by class name
        isDesOrd - Sort in descending order or not: true - descending order /false - ascending order
        tabLength - Desired TAB length with integer value larger than 0
        resultFormat - Result format: 0 - standard format suitable for console delimited by TAB/ 1 - comma separated value
        before - Path name to histogram file before memory leak
        after - Path name to histogram file after memory leak. If this parameter is null, this method just sort histogram set as "before" parameter.
        Returns:
        Object array merged and sorted according to condition
        Throws:
        quitada.MononovException - Any exceptions while happening merging jmap histograms
        Since:
        0.4.5
